t\nunsuccessfully erupts out, into thermal emissions is responsible for the strong\nlate phase found in a confined flare. Besides, with some cases we illustrate\nthe signatures of the flare thermodynamic process in the chromosphere and\ntransition region in TDS charts. These results provide new clues to advance our\nunderstanding of the thermodynamic processes of solar flares and associated\nsolar eruptions, e.g., coronal mass ejections.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 31 Jul 2015 14:43:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 1 Sep 2015 14:42:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 17 Jan 2016 16:03:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-11"}
